The herald and news. (Newberry S.C.), 08 Feb. 1916. Page 2, Cols 1 and 2
   <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn86063758/1916-02-08/ed-1/seq-2/" rel="nofollow">chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn86063758/1916-02-08/ed-...</a>
says, &quot;Francis Charles Fuller, chief commissioner of Ashanti, was the first Englishman to set foot on American soil. Smiling broadly, he stepped out upon the hotel lawn, pacing back and forth on the turf as eagerly as a small boy at the opening of the barefoot season. He told the first complete story of the capture of the Appam and her voyage across the Atlantic.&quot;
